        {
            "title": "FedEx beats Q1 estimates but faces $1B loss due to US de minimis policy change, impacts international trade.",
            "id": "abb09613-3d60-410d-b12f-32fbd021a447",
            "description": "FedEx Corp. (NYSE: FDX) reported a strong first quarter for fiscal year 2026 with robust U.S. domestic growth and cost-cutting measures. Despite beating estimates, they anticipate a $1 billion hit for the full year due to the removal of the de minimis trade exemption, a policy change from the Trump administration. This exemption allowed duty-free entry for goods valued under $800, significantly impacting FedEx's Asia-to-U.S. shipping lanes. CFO John Dietrich confirmed the $1 billion impact includes lost opportunities and trade-related expenses. This change is expected to affect international trade, especially in cross-border e-commerce.",
            "link": "https://www.markets.news/headlines/abb09613-3d60-410d-b12f-32fbd021a447",
            "pub_date": "2025-09-19 14:50:04",
